              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">The Maori fight</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-nov-23-1.jpg" alt="The Maori fight" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Thousands of Māori individuals and supporters are <a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2024/11/19/why-are-new-zealands-maori-protesting-over-colonial-era-treaty-bill" target="_blank">protesting</a> against the Treaty Principles Bill introduced by the ACT Party in New Zealand. The bill seeks to redefine the principles of the <a href="https://nzhistory.govt.nz/politics/treaty/the-treaty-in-brief" target="_blank">Treaty of Waitangi</a>, emphasizing equality among all citizens and aiming to eliminate “race-based politics.” Critics, including Māori activists, argue it undermines Māori rights and self-determination, protected in the Māori version of the Treaty.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Protests, including a significant nine-day <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/live/ckgrwem73gmt" target="_blank">hikoi</a>, have erupted. The protests also express broader discontent with government policies on Maori affairs. Although the protests are intense, the bill is unlikely to gain enough support in Parliament. There are undeniable ongoing tensions regarding Indigenous rights in New Zealand. There are significant <a href="https://teara.govt.nz/en/ethnic-inequalities" target="_blank">disparities</a> between the Maori and other New Zealanders on an institutional level regarding health, poverty, and education.  </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

